	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've wished for direct support for using $0F in the palette selection as Black, but use of $0D and $1D is there instead, and we've proven that in any TV using signals, using palettes $0D, $1D, $0E, $1E, $2E, $3E, is not recommended, I am not sure about $1F,$2F,$3F,<br /><br />Maybe you can turn them blacks to $0F by default, but make a toggle that gives them a warning about TVs not supporting some colors that are Pure Black if re-enabled, Benefiting the Use of $0F on any NES games created!.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


